                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/54b.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Letcher</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-06T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 6, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Represent to Carranza that Department is informed that in the Huasteca district
                    eighty miles south of Tampico, territory said to be controlled by the
                    Constitutionalists, Americans in charge of oil wells were, after returning
                    there, not allowed to remain and have been denied protection, whereas more
                    favorable treatment is accorded to foreigners other than Americans. Please
                    request him to give instructions to his commanders in that section to the end
                    that they will afford protection to all foreigners, including Americans, in that
                    important oil-producing district. Make same representations regarding Los
                    Esteros district, about thirty miles north of Tampico.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
